    "is_free": false,
    "description": "Predictile is an orthodox Twin Stick Shooter.<br><br>Except that the predictive lines of attack are displayed...<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3012290/extras/7beec7bb0fcf39c6fa9ecf34aedbb195.avif?t=1718898986\" width=508 height=258 /></span><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Check the predicted line and avoid it!</h2>Thanks to the predictive lines that are displayed, you have a long time to evade.<br>Instead of reflexes and dynamic vision, you need to be able to assess the situation and move to a place where you will not be hit by an attack.<br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3012290/extras/affdd17f9b481597bb126f1c35ae3535.poster.avif?t=1718898986\" width=562 height=278 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3012290/extras/affdd17f9b481597bb126f1c35ae3535.webm?t=1718898986\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3012290/extras/affdd17f9b481597bb126f1c35ae3535.mp4?t=1718898986\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Random gameplay</h2>This game is a so-called roguelike style game, with random enemy placement.<br>Not only are enemies randomly placed, but even enemies of the same type will have different movement speeds and bullet firing frequencies, so it's important to play around without being confused by the speed and pace.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Power-up items</h2>Players attack with manually aimed shots and auto-aim lasers,<br>and there are items available to increase various abilities such as attack power and range.<br><br>You can choose one of three items to acquire.<br>The item not selected will collide with a wall and disappear,<br>but depending on your movement and placement, you may have a chance to acquire two or more.<br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3012290/extras/7af556ff4604d82ba94d4019765ef945.poster.avif?t=1718898986\" width=582 height=290 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3012290/extras/7af556ff4604d82ba94d4019765ef945.webm?t=1718898986\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3012290/extras/7af556ff4604d82ba94d4019765ef945.mp4?t=1718898986\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Option</h2>There is also an option to adjust the length so that you can really feel the effect of the prediction line.<br><br>You can also have no prediction line at all like in a typical shooter game,<br>but this game is balanced around the assumption that there will be prediction lines, so we don't really recommend that...<br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3012290/extras/8a88aba17735dfae98cb7e174a055e14.poster.avif?t=1718898986\" width=582 height=290 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3012290/extras/8a88aba17735dfae98cb7e174a055e14.webm?t=1718898986\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3012290/extras/8a88aba17735dfae98cb7e174a055e14.mp4?t=1718898986\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span>",
